**Abstract:**
Essay titled "My Problem" addressing the challenge of doing philosophy of religion outside Greek categories. Argues Pascal's objection remains valid: "The God of philosophers is not the God of Jesus-Christ." Discusses difficulty of escaping philosophical theism as an intellectual and philosopher, given weight of tradition from medieval scholastics who submitted Christian faith to Greek categories. Emphasizes Christianity's God is "primarily historical" - freely irrupting into history, not deducible, intelligibly presented in Bible, transforming ongoing history - none of which fits Greek categories without radical distortion.

**AI Recommendation:** Keep in undated/notes - important essay on Xavier's central thesis

